Author: R  MASON
Vol / Page:
Edition:
Quote: A name given to smallish divaricating shrubs with dark stems and, often, small dark-green leaves: e.g. <i>Plagianthus betulinus, Coprosma propinqua, Hymenanthera</i> sp(p), <i>Aristotelia</i> sp(p) etc. These shrubs are sometimes clothed with a black fungus.
